The US will send auditors for final assessment of Kenya's viability to handle direct flights by the end of October. This was confirmed by US Transportation secretary Antony Fox who met Transport Cabinet secretary James Macharia at the sidelines of the 39th International Civil Aviation Organisation Assembly taking place in Montreal,Canada."Among other matters, the two ministers reviewed the progress made by Kenya in achieving category one status and thus allowing direct flights to USA," the ministry said in the statement.Macharia and his counterpart said most of outstanding issues had been concluded and the audit team from the US will be dispatched soon for final confirmation and sign off.The US Federal Aviation Administration inspectors are expected to assess the aviation security situation, operation capacity of the JKIA and the Kenya Civil Aviation Authority s capacity.Kenya has to meet eight critical elements under the FAA s Administration s International Aviation Safety Assessment procedure.